def printPredictOutput(df,predict):
    cdf = df.copy()
    cdf["gender"] = predict

    cdf['gender'] = leGender.inverse_transform(cdf['gender'])
    cdf['scarf'] = leScarf.inverse_transform(cdf['scarf'])
    cdf['beard'] = leBeard.inverse_transform(cdf['beard'])
    cdf['hair'] = leHair.inverse_transform(cdf['hair'])
    print("\n", cdf)
    
    print("\nAccuracy Score is: {:.0%}".format(accuracy_score(testData_output, predict)))
    print("Mean Squared Error is: {:.0%}".format(mean_squared_error(testData_output, predict)))

# Define a Function for showing tha Bar Chat of each Model
def printPredictBarChat(title, predict):
    lable = ["Accuracy","Error"]
    values = [ (100 * accuracy_score(testData_output, predict)),(100 * mean_squared_error(testData_output, predict))]
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize = (6, 5))   
    plt.bar(lable, values, color ='maroon', width = 0.3)
    
    plt.xlabel("Accuracy and Error")
    plt.ylabel("Total Percentage")
    plt.title(title)

    plt.show()
    
    
    
# Call Function through loop
count = 0
for x in prediction:
    count = count + 1
    print('\n')
    printmd('<b>{0}: Predicted OutPut of "{1}" Algorithm:</b>'.format(count ,x), color="blue")
    printPredictBarChat(x, prediction[x])

# Define a Function for showing tha Pie Chat of each Model
def printPredictPaiChat(title, predict):
    lable = ["Accuracy","Error"]
    values = [ (100 * accuracy_score(testData_output, predict)),(100 * mean_squared_error(testData_output, predict))]
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize = (8, 6))   
    plt.pie(values, labels = lable)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.show()

Create some Function for validate input

In [96]:
# check input is float or not
def check_user_input(val):
    while(1):
        try:
             # Convert it into float
            val = int(val)
            return val
        except ValueError:
             val = input("No.. Please Enter Valid Input:")

# check input is in given value or not
def check_user_hair(val):
    while(val.lower() != "bald" and val.lower() != "long" and val.lower() != "short" and val.lower() != "medium"):
        val = input("No.. Please Enter Valid Input:")
       
    if(val.lower() == "bald"):
        return "Bald"
    elif(val.lower() == "long"):
        return "Long"
    elif(val.lower() == "short"):
        return "Short"
    else:
        return "Medium"


# check input is in yes or no      
def check_user_BS(val):
    while(val.lower() != "no" and val.lower() != "yes"):
        val = input("No.. Please Enter Valid Input:")
       
    if(val.lower() == "no"):
        return "No"
    else:
        return "Yes"

Create Function for getting Unseen Data¶

  • This Function will get user input and doing some preprocessing like exterect feature and lable encoding etc
  • Than pass this input or unseen data to model and pridict some output
  • Lable Decode that pridicted output and shows the pridiction result in human readable form
In [97]:
#function For get user input
def unseenData():
    #input from user
    height = input("Please Enter Your Height ( in centimeter):")
    height = check_user_input(height)

    weight = input("Please Enter Your weight ( in pounds):")
    weight = check_user_input(weight)

    hair = input("Please Enter Your Hair Length ( Bald/Long/Short/Medium):")
    hair = check_user_hair(hair)

    beard = input("Do You Have Beard? ( Yes/No):")
    beard = check_user_BS(beard)

    scarf = input("Do You wear Scarf? ( Yes/No):")
    scarf = check_user_BS(scarf)


    #store user input in DataFrame
    userInput = pd.DataFrame({'height': height,
                              'weight': weight, 
                              'hair': [hair,'Medium','Short','Bald'], 
                              'beard': [beard,'Yes','No','No'],
                              'scarf': [scarf,'Yes','No','No'] 
                             })

    #Display input DataFrame
    print("\n\nUser Input or Unsean Data:\n")
    print(tabulate(userInput.loc[:0,:], headers='keys', tablefmt='psql'))


    #lable indoding  on input data 
    userInput['scarf'] = leScarf.fit_transform(userInput['scarf'])
    userInput['beard'] = leBeard.fit_transform(userInput['beard'])
    userInput['hair'] = leHair.fit_transform(userInput['hair'])

    #show incoded data 
    print("\nUser Input After Lable Encoding:\n")
    print(tabulate(userInput.loc[:0,:], headers='keys', tablefmt='psql'))

    #Pass input to Model for prediction
    userOutput = rfc.predict(userInput)
    #lable decoding
    userOutput = leGender.inverse_transform(userOutput)
    #display model prediction
    print() #display colored output
    printmd('Pridicted Output by Model: <b>"{0}"</b>'.format(userOutput[0]), color="blue")
    print()
